  <num>47-404</num>
  <heading>Account books of Collector.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>It shall be the duty of the Collector to keep in his office account books, in which shall be entered:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>The dates of payment of all taxes;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>The amounts paid;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>The names of the persons by whom payment has been made;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(4)</num>
      <text>The years paid for;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(5)</num>
      <text>The property paid on; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(6)</num>
      <text>The names of the persons to whom assessed.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>His books shall at all times be open to the inspection of any officer who may be authorized by the Mayor of the District of Columbia to examine the same.</text>
  </para>
